<p>The Equations (3) and (4) are called <alert>rotation formulas</alert>. It follows that if the angle of rotation <em>θ</em> is given, then Equation (3) can be used to determine the <em>x</em> and <em>y</em> coordinates of a point P if we know its <em>x</em>′ and <em>y</em>′ coordinates. Similarly, Equation (4) can be used to determine the <em>x</em>′ and <em>y</em>′ coordinates of P if we know its <em>x</em> and <em>y</em> coordinates.</p>
